This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, To evaluate the effectiveness/relative effectiveness and tolerability of pharmacological interventions for the prevention of radiation-induced salivary gland dysfunction., The following null hypotheses will be tested for comparisons between groups:, There is no difference in the proportion of patients acquiring salivary gland dysfunction (SGD) or the severity of SGD and its associated oral complaints following radiation therapy in a group receiving preventative pharmacological interventions for SGD compared with a group receiving no intervention/placebo., There is no difference in the proportion of patients acquiring salivary gland dysfunction (SGD) or the severity of SGD and its associated oral complaints following radiation therapy in a group receiving one preventative pharmacological intervention compared with a group receiving another pharmacological intervention for SGD